Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

When boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use #scissors{} if easier).

Zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Drain the @king prawns{150%g}. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, prawns and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount).

Bring the sauce to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the prawns are cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Stir the @peas{120%g}, @Orkney crab meat{100%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} through the sauce until melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the lemon zest, cooked linguine and half the chives. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Remove from the heat and add a good squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lemon juice if needed.

Share your creamy crab and prawn linguine between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining chives. Top with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side drizzled with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!